				I don't understand you people.<BR>
<BR>
You say that it is unfair that they got a sword for attending an event and winning contests, and either you did not or could not go.<BR>
<BR>
How in hell is this not fair?<BR>
<BR>
They took their own time and travelled to baltimore to participate in an event, and thus were rewarded.<BR>
<BR>
Isn't the basic concept of Everquest risk/time invested and reward?<BR>
<BR>
Let's look at an example: Some people go on a dragon raid. You are unable to attend. Should you get one of the awesome weapons that are dropped?<BR>
<BR>
Some people really make me sick. The same goes for the people who complain about not getting as many rewards because they only play an hour a day.<BR>
<BR>
OF COURSE the people who play more should get more rewards! Sure they are paying the same 10 dollars, but they are INVESTING MORE TIME IN THE GAME.<BR>
<BR>
Here is a real life example: You want concert tickets. You know that they will sell out fast. You get on line 2 days in advance, and stay there until the ticket booth opens up. Some people come along 5 minutes beforehand and pick up the tickets that you wanted, so you didn't get them. Is that fair? Of course not.<BR>
<BR>
That concludes my rant. Thank you. If you don't like it (or do like it) tell me what you think. I want to hear.<BR>
<BR>
Kalverian of the United Souls<BR>
Luclin
